Request

Request is responsible for receiving and parsing income HTTP requests.

Built for receiving communication from other sources, Request has the ability to take a request, parse the headers, get the data, determine what kind of requests, and other features.

Example:

$request = new Request();

if($request -> isAjaxRequest()) {
    echo "AJAX REQUEST\n";
}

if(strtolower($request -> getRequestMethod()) =='post') {
    echo "A Post Request was send\n";
}

$data = getRequestData();
print_r($data);
